Mongol;;76;;87;;R;;This fact-based epic traces the early and tumultuous years of legendary warrior Genghis Khan, then known as Temudgin (Tadanobu Asano). Despite the killing of his father, the betrayal of his friend, and even being forced to serve as a slave, Temudgin still creates his own path for future greatness. He hones his battle skills and marries Borte (Khulan Chuluun), whose love and reliability are crucial, often overlooked elements to his historic success as a conqueror.;;Biography,History,Adventure,Drama,War;;Sergey Bodrov;;2007;;Tadanobu Asano,Honglei Sun,Khulan Chuluun,Amadu Mamadakov,Bayertsetseg Erdenebat,Amarbold Tuvshinbayar,Tegen Ao,Sai Xing Ga;;https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/mongol